==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shovelnose
<hw>Shov"el*nose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The common sand shark. See under <er>Snad</er>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A small California shark (<spn>Heptranchias
maculatus</spn>), which is taken for its oil.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A
Pacific Ocean shark (<spn>Hexanchus corinus</spn>).</def> <sd>(d)</sd>
<def>A ganoid fish of the Sturgeon family (<spn>Scaphirhynchus
platyrhynchus</spn>) of the Mississippi and Ohio rivers; -- called also
<altname>white sturgeon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shovel-nosed</ent>⟦br⟧
